Package SudokuGUI

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ButtonPanel
    This class stores all the buttons that the player will use, and their functions in the game.
    GameFrame
    This class basically covers all of the visible parts of the GUI interface except for the Stopwatch clock, which is set in its own specific class.
    LoginArrays
    This class basically holds the different arrays for the Sudoku game according to each of their difficulty level in which the player could choose at the beginning of the game
    SingleSudokuPanel
    This class basically creates a single sudoku panel, which is where the sudoku board should go.
    Stopwatch
    This class basically creates a separate interface which holds the time (and also the points) that have passed since the user started the game.
    SudokuCell
    This class draws out each of the specific cells in the Sudoku game board.
    SudokuGame
    This class basically starts the sudoku game; the user runs the code from here.
    ToggleListener
    SetToggleButtons: This method is used to store the values of the Button array in a JToggleButton.
    UserTypeInputListener
    This class, in comparison to toggle, stores the Mouse Listeners and the get value methods of the cell than the Button listeners.
